00:32:17,020 --> 00:32:20,185
You feel it, Will?
This is what it's all about!

513
00:32:26,737 --> 00:32:30,447
You know the rules!
There are no rules!

514
00:32:30,825 --> 00:32:33,600
Last man standing walks away!

515
00:32:33,725 --> 00:32:35,955
And start fighting. Right!

516
00:32:37,465 --> 00:32:38,622
Come on, fight!

517
00:32:39,655 --> 00:32:41,455
Fight! Fight!

518
00:32:42,165 --> 00:32:43,165
Fight!

519
00:32:43,925 --> 00:32:45,025
Fight!

520
00:32:45,225 --> 00:32:46,046
Camden!

521
00:32:47,345 --> 00:32:49,508
Come on, you freaks, let's fight!

522
00:33:01,187 --> 00:33:02,187
That's it!

523
00:33:16,615 --> 00:33:18,265
His vitals are spiking.

524
00:33:20,325 --> 00:33:21,999
- Trouble.
- What?

525
00:33:22,445 --> 00:33:24,690
The front pair, doomsday wired.

526
00:33:24,815 --> 00:33:27,280
Completely enmeshed
in his peripheral nerve.

527
00:33:27,405 --> 00:33:28,855
And if it gets cut?

528
00:33:29,125 --> 00:33:30,675
So does his lifeline.

529
00:33:39,476 --> 00:33:42,186
<i>You were born in Devonshire
in 1829...</i>

530
00:33:44,185 --> 00:33:45,518
<i>110 over 70.</i>

531
00:33:46,285 --> 00:33:47,535
<i>Blood's moving.</i>

532
00:33:53,596 --> 00:33:56,074
- Hang on, father.
- I'm trying.

533
00:34:02,245 --> 00:34:04,940
Mom, he's in a lot of pain.
Can't you knock him out or something?

534
00:34:05,065 --> 00:34:06,584
I need him conscious.

535
00:34:09,005 --> 00:34:11,035
<i>Once you enter this door,</i>

536
00:34:11,912 --> 00:34:14,677
<i>you are on a path
that cannot be reversed...</i>

537
00:34:15,220 --> 00:34:17,035
<i>Cannot be reversed...</i>

538
00:34:23,545 --> 00:34:24,975
<i>Well, Gregory,</i>

539
00:34:25,195 --> 00:34:27,564
you've designed
the perfect fighting machine.

540
00:34:29,819 --> 00:34:32,675
You don't know
the hell you'll unleash.

541
00:34:33,405 --> 00:34:34,706
Can you hear me?

542
00:34:35,074 --> 00:34:37,274
Get it out of me!

543
00:34:37,805 --> 00:34:39,155
I need your help.

544
00:34:40,872 --> 00:34:43,080
I'm the patient, for god's sake.

545
00:34:44,025 --> 00:34:47,655
You were also the most able surgeon
the Royal College ever produced.

546
00:34:49,335 --> 00:34:51,535
These last pincers
are the neural tap.

547
00:34:51,660 --> 00:34:54,160
How do I separate them
without killing you?

548
00:34:57,565 --> 00:34:59,555
The Norwich... Giant.

549
00:35:00,545 --> 00:35:01,545
The what?

550
00:35:02,615 --> 00:35:03,985
Mom, what did he say?

551
00:35:04,110 --> 00:35:07,135
A pituitary abnormal
on a hair-trigger to self-destruct.

552
00:35:07,835 --> 00:35:09,840
Isolate the creature's neural
kill switch,

553
00:35:09,965 --> 00:35:12,145
cut it before it can send
the signal.

554
00:35:12,725 --> 00:35:14,175
Sounds like a plan.

555
00:35:15,225 --> 00:35:17,825
Except the Norwich Giant
died on the table.

556
00:35:35,383 --> 00:35:36,550
Nice. Lovely.

557
00:36:24,375 --> 00:36:27,225
I've exposed the peripheral nerve
where it's been hijacked.

558
00:36:28,235 --> 00:36:29,811
I have the cut point.

559
00:36:35,975 --> 00:36:37,026
Do it, mom.

560
00:36:52,835 --> 00:36:55,046
Game's over.
Back down.

561
00:36:55,235 --> 00:36:57,045
Let's get on with it!

562
00:36:57,905 --> 00:36:59,805
Come on. Get him out!

563
00:37:00,725 --> 00:37:02,761
Fight! Fight!

564
00:37:12,355 --> 00:37:14,898
All right, all right, you two.

565
00:37:15,275 --> 00:37:16,525
Let's go!

566
00:37:19,285 --> 00:37:21,155
Here we go!

567
00:37:27,779 --> 00:37:28,829
Look at me!

568
00:37:39,735 --> 00:37:40,935
Got it.

569
00:37:47,474 --> 00:37:50,017
D&S... Meat packing...

570
00:37:55,425 --> 00:37:56,925
I'll get an address.

571
00:38:20,275 --> 00:38:22,131
I think we have a winner.

572
00:38:28,235 --> 00:38:29,235
Love it.

573
00:38:29,805 --> 00:38:30,875
Come on.

574
00:38:41,505 --> 00:38:43,255
This is your time, right?

575
00:38:43,935 --> 00:38:46,575
Is that what you said?
Is this what you want?

576
00:38:47,085 --> 00:38:50,365
Is this what you want?
Is this what you all want?

577
00:38:52,495 --> 00:38:53,495
Get up!

578
00:38:56,125 --> 00:38:57,125
Get up!

579
00:38:58,878 --> 00:39:00,711
Finish him, you dumb bastard!

580
00:39:01,055 --> 00:39:02,055
Come on!

581
00:39:10,175 --> 00:39:11,639
It's me, Henry.

582
00:39:16,875 --> 00:39:18,647
This isn't you!
This isn't you.

583
00:39:18,815 --> 00:39:20,065
Come on! Come...

584
00:39:23,505 --> 00:39:24,986
Will, this is not you.

585
00:39:31,285 --> 00:39:33,078
Help... Help me.

586
00:39:33,875 --> 00:39:36,915
Come on! Kill him! Let's go!

587
00:39:41,855 --> 00:39:43,455
Stand down!

588
00:39:47,969 --> 00:39:49,885
- Help me.
- You're going to be okay.

589
00:39:50,054 --> 00:39:51,555
You're going to be okay.

590
00:39:51,723 --> 00:39:55,016
Listen to me. The first thing we gotta
do is get that thing out of you, okay?

591
00:40:08,535 --> 00:40:11,615
You think you're breaking up
some fights? You have no idea

592
00:40:11,784 --> 00:40:15,055
- who you're messing with.
- Pass the same message onto the Cabal.

593
00:40:26,075 --> 00:40:28,799
- What do you want?
- I want these fights stopped.

594
00:40:29,111 --> 00:40:31,011
And the genetic experiments.

595
00:40:31,205 --> 00:40:33,888
You surface someplace else,
and we'll be waiting.

596
00:40:35,535 --> 00:40:36,605
All right.

597
00:40:38,035 --> 00:40:39,155
All right!

598
00:40:46,845 --> 00:40:48,495
This is the last cycle.

599
00:40:49,225 --> 00:40:52,230
All signs are that your body
has purged the abnormality.

600
00:40:52,355 --> 00:40:53,905
Danny's not far behind.

601
00:40:56,705 --> 00:40:58,655
I keep thinking, was that me,

602
00:40:59,145 --> 00:41:01,235
ready to kill a friend, or was it...

603
00:41:02,165 --> 00:41:03,365
somebody else?

604
00:41:04,825 --> 00:41:07,055
We all have
the impulse for violence.

605
00:41:07,515 --> 00:41:09,515
The true measure of a species,

606
00:41:09,725 --> 00:41:12,225
indeed, of a person,
is in our restraint.

607
00:41:23,035 --> 00:41:25,415
- Oh, my God. Danny...
- Kayla.

608
00:41:29,405 --> 00:41:30,585
Oh, my God.

609
00:41:32,385 --> 00:41:33,615
I love you.

610
00:41:34,645 --> 00:41:35,805
Thank you.

611
00:41:40,875 --> 00:41:43,795
The first 10 years after you were gone
were the hardest.

612
00:41:44,235 --> 00:41:46,825
I kept asking myself,
"what would father do?"

613
00:41:51,145 --> 00:41:52,785
I can't stay here, Helen.

614
00:41:56,485 --> 00:41:57,485
Why not?

615
00:41:58,145 --> 00:42:01,735
I have decades I haven't touched on.
So much I need to show you.

616
00:42:03,125 --> 00:42:06,875
The longer I'm here, the greater risk
I pose to your well-being.

617
00:42:08,615 --> 00:42:12,395
I wanted one day to come back
to help protect you from your enemies,

618
00:42:13,145 --> 00:42:14,697
not to wind up helping them.

619
00:42:14,822 --> 00:42:17,242
The Cabal had already asserted
themselves as a threat long

620
00:42:17,410 --> 00:42:19,369
before they tapped your expertise.

621
00:42:20,825 --> 00:42:23,815
I admit, their engineered warrior,
the one you designed,

622
00:42:24,405 --> 00:42:25,955
that does make me worry.

623
00:42:26,325 --> 00:42:27,919
When I finally put it down,

624
00:42:29,445 --> 00:42:33,355
it had taken the life
of every abnormal in my laboratory.

625
00:42:34,775 --> 00:42:37,745
Then who better to find
its weakness than you?

626
00:42:38,645 --> 00:42:41,415
And what better place than here,
in the Sanctuary?

627
00:42:42,715 --> 00:42:43,775
I'm sorry.

628
00:42:44,495 --> 00:42:46,725
I'll have to seek
my own way for now.

629
00:42:49,505 --> 00:42:51,095
But I promise you, Helen,

630
00:42:53,035 --> 00:42:54,435
I'll never be far.

